ult is a remarkably comprehensive view of London 'the writer's writer.'" —American Literary Realism "An absorbing account of how hard the writer worked to learn his craft. . . . We find a master prose stylist concerned with problems of selectivity and concrete issues of tone, form, atmosphere, and point of view." —Modern Philology "A remarkable collection. . . . This is a firsthand look at a writer's honest and forthright opinions on his craft." —Los Angeles Times  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / American / General.2bisacsh1 aReesman, Jeanne Campbell, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWalker, Dale L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361819040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503618190423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503618190/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles